ce:section.ce:para:
To check the accuracy of the developed fluorescence probe, the method was employed to the detection of total Cr and Cr(III) in the GSB07-1187-2000 and GSB07-3174-2014 certified reference materials for environmental water, respectively. The results show that there are in good agreement with the certified valuesin Table 1. The method was also used for the detecting of Cr(VI) and Cr(III) species in several environmental water samples. As shown in Table 2
                        , when different concentrations of Cr(VI) and Cr(III) solutions were spiked in water samples, the recoveries of the method for Cr(VI) and Cr(III) in water samples were from 94 to 107% with the relative standard deviation (RSD) lower than 4.5. These results indicate that the established method based on CQDs as fluorescence probes is suitable for the quantitative determination of Cr(VI) and Cr(III) in the environmental water samples. Compared to other detection method for Cr(VI), CQDs fluorescent probe exhibited a wide linearity range for Cr(VI) (Table 3
                        ).
